:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"Rob\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1353:\"<p>As you might have <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ModernTribeInc/status/394923614635454464\">seen us tease</a> earlier this week on Twitter, we&#8217;ve been working on a whirlwind of a project with our friend <a href=\"https://twitter.com/pippinsplugins\">Pippin Williamson</a> recently. Today we&#8217;re stoked to finally show you the fruits of those labors: <strong>EDD Tickets</strong>, a new add-on for <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/the-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a> and <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/easy-digital-downloads/\">Easy Digital Downloads</a> that allows you to sell event tickets using EDD as your commerce engine.</p>\n<p>Check out this quick preview video for an overview of the setup and use:</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/78122977\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<p>We&#8217;re still ironing out a few of the features, including a nifty option to download your ticket directly from the purchase confirmation page, which will be included in the final release. As for a timeline &#8212; that&#8217;ll depend on what we dig up in the QA process this week. We&#8217;re optimistic based on what we&#8217;ve seen so far and hope to have this available for download sometime in the coming weeks. Stay tuned!</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"http://tri.be/easy-digital-download